  <title>Repeat your music</title>

  <p><app>Rhythmbox</app> stops playback after all tracks have been played from the <gui>Music</gui> library. However, you can set <app>Rhythmbox</app> to repeat tracks. To set repeatition of tracks:</p>

  <steps>
    <item>
      <p>Click on <gui style="button">Repeat</gui> icon in the
      <app>Rhythmbox</app> toolbar.</p>
    </item>
  </steps>

  <note style="important">
    <p>If you have <link xref="shuffle-music">
    <gui style="button">Shuffle</gui></link> mode enabled along with
    <gui style="button">Repeat</gui> then, <app>Rhythmbox</app> will play all
    tracks in the <gui>Play Queue</gui> in random order. Once all tracks have
    been played, <app>Rhythmbox</app> will repeat tracks from the <gui>Play Queue</gui> by playing them again, randomly.</p>
  </note>

  <note style="tip">
    <p>You can also repeat tracks by pressing 
    <keyseq><key>Ctrl</key><key>R</key></keyseq>.</p>
  </note>

